        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Mindseed - Aundh"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Surya Rao"
          },
          "datePublished": "2023-04-13",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "School is good but the management /Principal should brief the parents about all the conditions before taking the first installment. After paying the first installment, now you are saying kits will not be given if post dated cheque are not submitted by 20th April 2022 for the June and sept.\nI feal the school should not send such message to parents.\nIf there is any due of payment then you can say whatever it may be for future installments don't behave like this",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Mindseed - Aundh"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Preeti Ravindran"
          },
          "datePublished": "2023-03-17",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "4",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Annual day event organised by Mindseed was a great experience. The event was well-organized, and I appreciate the efforts of the teachers and the wonderful preparation by the students.\n\nThe event showcased the talents of the students and their hard work in various areas, including music, dance, drama, and more. The performances were top-notch, and it was clear that the students had put in a lot of time and effort to make the event a success.\n\nHowever, one thing that left me disappointed was the fact that tickets were unavailable for Ridhaan's grandparents. It's understandable that tickets may be limited, but it would have been nice to see more effort made to accommodate grandparents who were unable to attend. This could have been a great opportunity for grandparents to see their grandchildren's achievements and celebrate their accomplishments.\n\nOverall, despite the disappointment with the ticket availability, I still appreciate the efforts of everyone involved in organizing the event. Mindseed's annual day was a great showcase of the talents and achievements of the students and I look forward to attending future events.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
